        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 5:29PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 529 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles south of Afton, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Santa Teresa, Chamberino, La Union, and Union Pacific Intermodal
Terminal.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
